### ==================== USER ACCOUNT ====================

### 1. Register a new user
POST http://localhost:54955/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "regular@example.com",
    "password": "password123",
    "firstName": "Regular",
    "lastName": "User"
}

### 2. Login as regular user
POST http://localhost:54955/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "regular@example.com",
    "password": "password123"
}

### Save the USER_TOKEN from response

### 3. User can view products (public - no token needed)
GET http://localhost:54955/api/products

### 4. User can access their cart (needs authentication)
GET http://localhost:54955/api/cart
Authorization: Bearer USER_TOKEN

### 5. User can create orders
POST http://localhost:54955/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer USER_TOKEN

{
    "shippingAddress": "123 User St",
    "billingAddress": "123 User St",
    "paymentMethod": "CREDIT_CARD"
}

### 6. User CANNOT access admin endpoints (should return 403 Forbidden)
GET http://localhost:54955/api/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer USER_TOKEN

### ==================== ADMIN ACCOUNT ====================

### 7. Login as admin
POST http://localhost:54955/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "admin@ecommerce.com",
    "password": "admin123"
}

### Save the ADMIN_TOKEN from response

### 8. Admin can view all users
GET http://localhost:54955/api/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer ADMIN_TOKEN

### 9. Admin can update user roles
PUT http://localhost:54955/api/admin/users/2/role?role=ADMIN
Authorization: Bearer ADMIN_TOKEN

### 10. Admin can view all orders
GET http://localhost:54955/api/admin/orders
Authorization: Bearer ADMIN_TOKEN

### 11. Admin can update order status
PUT http://localhost:54955/api/admin/orders/1/status?status=CONFIRMED
Authorization: Bearer ADMIN_TOKEN

### 12. Admin can view dashboard stats
GET http://localhost:54955/api/admin/stats
Authorization: Bearer ADMIN_TOKEN